The paper deals with dynamic problems related to matrices and graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper presents improved algorithms for maintaining the inverse of a matrix undergoing updates, which is a fundamental data structure problem. The paper also deals with graph problems such as maintaining reachability, distances, and maximum matching size, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions the use of fast matrix multiplication, which is a topic in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
